Name: AccountCurrencyCode
Notes: The currency of the Customer account.

Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AccountTimeZone
Notes: Name of the timezone selected for the Customer account. For example: "(GMT-05:00) Eastern Time". This field does not reflect the current state of daylight saving time for the timezone.

Name: ActiveViewCpm
Notes: Average cost of viewable impressions (ActiveViewImpressions).

Name: ActiveViewCtr
Notes: How often people clicked your ad after it became viewable. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewImpressions
Notes: How often your ad has become viewable on a Display Network site.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurability
Notes: The ratio of impressions that could be measured by Active View over the number of served impressions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableCost
Notes: The cost of the impressions you received that were measurable by Active View.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableImpressions
Notes: The number of times your ads are appearing on placements in positions where they can be seen.

Name: ActiveViewViewability
Display Name: Active View viewable impr. / measurable impr.
Notes: The percentage of time when your ad appeared on an Active View enabled site (measurable impressions) and was viewable (viewable impressions). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AdvertisingChannelSubType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Unknown
SEARCH_MOBILE_APP / Search Mobile App
DISPLAY_MOBILE_APP / Display Mobile App
SEARCH_EXPRESS / Search Express
DISPLAY_EXPRESS / Display Express
UNIVERSAL_APP_CAMPAIGN / Universal App Campaign
Notes: Optional refinement of the campaign's AdvertisingChannelType.

Name: AdvertisingChannelType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Unknown
SEARCH / Search
DISPLAY / Display
SHOPPING / Shopping
VIDEO / Video
MULTI_CHANNEL / Multi Channel
EXPRESS / Express
Notes: Primary serving target for ads in the campaign.

Name: AllConversionRate
Notes: AllConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Amount
Notes: The daily budget. On the Campaign Performance Report this column reflects the entire shared budget if the campaign draws from a shared budget.

Name: AverageCost
Notes: The average amount you pay per interaction. This amount is the total cost of your ads divided by the total number of interactions.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpe
Notes: The average amount that you've been charged for an ad engagement. This amount is the total cost of all ad engagements divided by the total number of ad engagements. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AverageCpv
Notes: The average amount you pay each time someone views your ad. The average CPV is defined by the total cost of all ad views divided by the number of views. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageFrequency
Notes: Average number of times a unique cookie was exposed to your ad over a given time period. Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AveragePageviews
Notes: Average number of pages viewed per session. Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageTimeOnSite
Notes: Total duration of all sessions (in seconds) / number of sessions. Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: BaseCampaignId
Notes: The ID of base campaign of trial campaigns. For regular campaigns, this is equal to CampaignId.

Name: BiddingStrategyId
Notes: The ID of the BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: BiddingStrategyName
Notes: The name of the BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: BidType

To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: BudgetId
Notes: The ID of the Budget.

Name: CampaignDesktopBidModifier
Notes: Desktop bid modifier override at the campaign level. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignGroupId
Notes: The ID of campaign group.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignMobileBidModifier
Notes: Mobile bid modifier of the campaign. To filter by this field, use values greater than 0 and less than or equal to 1. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignTabletBidModifier
Notes: Tablet bid modifier override at the campaign level. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignTrialType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
BASE / base campaign
DRAFT / draft campaign
TRIAL / trial campaign
Notes: The type of campaign. This shows if the campaign is a trial campaign or not.

Name: ClickAssistedConversions
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign contributed to one or more assisted clicks. This field is formatted using US locale, i.e., using comma "," for thousands and dot "." for decimals.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Click Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign received in assisted clicks divided by the total number of conversions for which it triggered the last click. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign triggered assisted clicks. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ClickType
Enum Values:
URL_CLICKS / Headline
CALLS / Phone calls
OTHER / Other
PRODUCT_EXTENSION_CLICKS / Product plusbox offer
SITELINKS / Sitelink
PRODUCT_LISTING_AD_CLICKS / Shopping ad - Standard
GET_DIRECTIONS / Driving direction
OFFER_PRINTS / Print offer
BREADCRUMBS / Breadcrumbs

MOBILE_CALL_TRACKING / Mobile phone calls
LOCATION_EXPANSION / Get location details
STORE_LOCATOR / Show nearby locations
APP_DEEPLINK / App engagement ad deep link
PRICE_EXTENSION / Price Extension
VIDEO_WEBSITE_CLICKS / Website

VIDEO_APP_STORE_CLICKS / App store

VIDEO_END_CAP_CLICKS / End cap
CLICK_ON_ENGAGEMENT_AD / Click on engagement ad

LOCATION_FORMAT_LANDING_PAGE / Go to landing page
LOCATION_FORMAT_STORE_INFO / Go to store info
LOCATION_FORMAT_DIRECTIONS / Directions
LOCATION_FORMAT_CALL / Call
LOCATION_FORMAT_TEXT / Text
LOCATION_FORMAT_IMAGE / Image(s)
BROADBAND_PLAN / Broadband Plan
WIRELESS_PLAN / Wireless Plan
VISUAL_SITELINKS / Visual Sitelinks
PROMOTION_EXTENSION / Promotion Extension
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_HEADLINE / Ad Headline
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SWIPES / Swipes
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SEE_MORE / See More
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_ONE / Sitelink 1
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_TWO / Sitelink 2
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_THREE / Sitelink 3
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_FOUR / Sitelink 4
SWIPEABLE_GALLERY_AD_SITELINK_FIVE / Sitelink 5
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: Indicates the click type for metric fields such as Impressions. Since ads that serve can be attributed to multiple click types, metric fields may be double-counted and thus totals may not be accurate, especially for Display network campaigns.

Name: ContentBudgetLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percent of times that your ad was eligible to show on the Display Network but didn't because your budget was too low. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "> 90%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ContentImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions you've received on the Display Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ContentRankLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percentage of impressions on the Display Network that your ads didn't receive due to poor Ad Rank. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "> 90%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: A category that describes the action the user will take to complete a conversion. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned. Values: "Download", "Lead", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "View of a key page", and "Other".

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionTrackerId
Notes: ID of the conversion tracker.

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: The name of the conversion type. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerAllConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by all conversions.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: The Cost attributable to conversion-tracked clicks divided by the number of conversions

Name: CostPerCurrentModelAttributedConversion
Notes: Shows how your historic CostPerConversion data would look under the attribution model you've currently selected. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your AllConversions column. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CurrentModelAttributedConversions
Notes: Shows how your historic Conversions data would look under the attribution model you've currently selected. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CurrentModelAttributedConversionValue
Notes: Shows how your historic ConversionValue data would look under the attribution model you've currently selected. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek

MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: EndDate
Notes: The end date of the campaign, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: EngagementRate
Notes: How often people engage with your ad after it's shown to them. This is the number of ad expansions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Engagements
Notes: The number of engagements. An engagement occurs when a viewer expands your Lightbox ad. Also, in the future, other ad types may support engagement metrics.

Name: EnhancedCpcEnabled
Notes: Indicates if enhanced CPC is enabled on the bidding strategy.

Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other

ENGAGEMENT / Engagement ads
WEBSITE_CALL_METRICS / Calls from website
STORE_VISITS / Store visits
ANDROID_IN_APP / Android in-app action
ANDROID_DOWNLOAD / Android app install (from Google Play)
IOS_IN_APP / iOS in-app action

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: GmailForwards
Notes: The number of times your ad was forwarded to someone else as a message.

Name: GmailSaves
Notes: The number of times someone has saved your Gmail ad to their inbox as a message.

Name: GmailSecondaryClicks
Notes: The number of clicks to your landing page on the expanded state of Gmail ads.

Name: HourOfDay
Notes: The hour of day as a number between 0 and 23, inclusive.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversions
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions prior to the last click. This field is formatted using US locale, i.e., using comma "," for thousands and dot "." for decimals.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Impr. Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions divided by the total number of conversions for which this object triggered the last click. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionValue
Notes: Total value of all conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ImpressionReach
Notes: Number of unique cookies that were exposed to your ad over a given time period, or the special value "< 100" if the number of cookies is less than 100.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: InteractionRate
Notes: How often people interact with your ad after it is shown to them. This is the number of interactions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Interactions
Notes: The number of interactions. An interaction is the main user action associated with an ad format--clicks for text and shopping ads, views for video ads, and so on.

Name: InteractionTypes
Notes: The types of interactions that are reflected in the Interactions, InteractionRate, and AverageCost columns.

Name: InvalidClickRate
Notes: The percentage ("x.xx%") of clicks filtered out of your total number of clicks (filtered + non-filtered clicks) during the reporting period. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: InvalidClicks
Notes: Number of clicks Google considers illegitimate and doesn't charge you for.

Name: IsBudgetExplicitlyShared
Notes: Indicates if the budget is a shared budget (true) or specific to the campaign (false).

Name: LabelIds
Notes:
List of label IDs for the main object of this row.
List elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: Labels
Notes:
List of label names for the main object of this row.
List elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Enum Values:

Name: NumOfflineImpressions
Notes: Number of offline phone impressions.

Name: NumOfflineInteractions
Notes: Number of offline phone calls.

Name: OfflineInteractionRate
Notes: Number of phone calls received (NumOfflineInteractions) divided by the number of times your phone number is shown (NumOfflineImpressions). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: PercentNewVisitors
Notes: Percentage of first-time sessions (from people who had never visited your site before), formatted as "x.xx%". Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Period
Notes: Period over which to spend the budget.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: RelativeCtr
Notes: Your clickthrough rate (Ctr) divided by the average clickthrough rate of all advertisers on the websites that show your ads. Measures how your ads perform on Display Network sites compared to other ads on the same sites. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchBudgetLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percent of times that your ad was eligible to show on the Search Network but didn't because your budget was too low. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "> 90%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchClickShare
Notes: The number of clicks you've received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of clicks you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchExactMatchImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions you've received divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive on the Search Network for search terms that matched your keywords exactly (or were close variants of your keyword), regardless of your keyword match types. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchImpressionShare
Notes: The impressions you've received on the Search Network divided by the estimated number of impressions you were eligible to receive. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "< 10%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: SearchRankLostImpressionShare
Notes: The estimated percentage of impressions on the Search Network that your ads didn't receive due to poor Ad Rank. A percentage returned as "xx.xx%", or the special value "> 90%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

SERVING / eligible
NONE / none

Notes:
Custom URL parameters of the main object of this row.
CustomParameters elements are returned in JSON map format.

Name: ValuePerAllConversion
Notes: The value, on average, of all conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerCurrentModelAttributedConversion
Notes: Shows how your historic ValuePerConversion data would look under the attribution model you've currently selected. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile100Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched all of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile25Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 25% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile50Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 50% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile75Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 75% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoViewRate
Notes: The number of views your TrueView video ad receives divided by its number of impressions, including thumbnail impressions for TrueView in-display ads. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoViews
Notes: The number of times your video ads were viewed.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees a Display network ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g. clicking on) another ad. This field is formatted using US locale, i.e., using comma "," for thousands and dot "." for decimals.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
